Excellent! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me provide a detailed report on the hooks directory structure, CSS variables, React Query usage, and styling patterns:

## Project Exploration Report: Hooks, CSS Variables, React Query & Styling

### 1. Custom Hooks Directory Structure

The project has specialized hooks in component-specific directories:

**Universe Component Hooks** (`client/src/components/Universe/hooks/`):
- `useCosmicGravity.js` - Physics simulation for star positioning with cooling/damping algorithms
- `useUniverseCamera.js` - Camera position management in 3D space
- `useRocketMode.js` - Rocket flight mode functionality
- `useConstellationLinkMode.js` - Constellation connection mode

**Stories Component Hooks** (`client/src/components/Stories/hooks/`):
- `useStoryData.js` - Data fetching hooks for stories, chapters, comments (useQuery, useInfiniteQuery)
- `useStoryMutations.js` - Story/chapter CRUD mutations with optimistic updates

**Note**: No dedicated `client/src/hooks/` directory exists. All hooks are component-scoped.

---

### 2. CSS Variables System (index.css & App.css)

#### Light Theme `:root`
```css
/* Semantic color tokens */
--bg-primary: #FAF9F6;           /* Main background */
--bg-secondary: #F3F1ED;         /* Secondary background */
--bg-hover: #EDEAE5;            /* Hover state */
--bg-elevated: #FFFFFF;         /* Elevated surfaces */
--bg-backdrop: rgba(250,249,246,0.75);        /* Glass morphism base */
--bg-backdrop-heavy: rgba(250,249,246,0.85);  /* Darker backdrop */
--bg-overlay: rgba(250,249,246,0.3);          /* Semi-transparent overlay */
--bg-pill: rgba(120,100,80,0.06);             /* Pill-shaped elements */
--bg-glass: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);           /* Glass effect */
--bg-glass-border: rgba(200,180,150,0.2);     /* Glass border color */

/* Text colors */
--text-primary: #1A1612;
--text-heading: #12100D;
--text-secondary: #6B6560;
--text-body: #8A8480;
--text-muted: #A8A29E;
--text-faint: #C0BBB5;
--text-separator: #D9D4CE;

/* Borders and shadows */
--border-light: rgba(120,100,80,0.12);
--border-card: rgba(120,100,80,0.08);
--shadow-card: 0 1px 4px rgba(80,60,40,0.06), 0 4px 16px rgba(80,60,40,0.04);
--shadow-modal: 0 8px 32px rgba(80,60,40,0.12);

/* Accent colors */
--accent-purple: #C4943E;  /* Primary gold/bronze */
--accent-dark: #1A1612;
--accent-sage: #8A9E7A;
--accent-amber: #D4A853;
--color-danger: #DC2626;
--color-success: #16A34A;
```

#### Dark Theme `[data-theme="dark"]`
- Inverted palette with darker backgrounds (#0C0C0C, #141414)
- Lighter text colors (#F0EBE3, #F5F0E8)
- Stronger shadows for depth
- Gold accents remain (#D4A853, #E0BA6A)

---

### 3. React Query Patterns

#### A. useQuery for Posts/Feed

**ExplorePage.jsx** - Main feed patterns:
```javascript
// Fetch monthly hottest journals
const { data: feedData, isLoading: isLoadingFeed } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ["explore-hottest-monthly-feed", userId, currentUtcMonthKey],
    queryFn: () => getMonthlyHottestJournals(userId, 10),
    refetchOnWindowFocus: false,
    staleTime: 15 * 1000,  // 15 seconds
});

// Search journals with debouncing
const { data: searchData, isLoading: isLoadingSearch } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ["explore-search", userId, committedSearchQuery],
    queryFn: () => searchJournals(committedSearchQuery, 10, userId),
    enabled: isSearchMode,  // Only run when search is active
    refetchOnWindowFocus: false,
    staleTime: 10 * 1000,
});

// Auto-suggestions while typing
const { data: suggestionData, isLoading: isSuggestionsLoading } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ["explore-suggestions", userId, debouncedSearchInput],
    queryFn: () => searchJournals(debouncedSearchInput, 6, userId),
    enabled: debouncedSearchInput.length >= 2 && isSearchFocused && searchType === "posts",
    staleTime: 10 * 1000,
});
```

**PostCards.jsx** - Infinite pagination:
```javascript
const { data, isLoading, hasNextPage, isFetchingNextPage, fetchNextPage } = useInfiniteQuery({
    queryKey: ['journals'],
    queryFn: ({ pageParam }) => getJournals(pageParam, userId, session?.access_token),
    initialPageParam: 0,
    getNextPageParam: (lastPage) => lastPage.nextCursor,
    refetchOnWindowFocus: false,
    staleTime: 10 * 1000,
});
```

#### B. useMutation for Posts

**useMutation.js** - Optimistic updates with rollback:
```javascript
// Bookmark mutation with optimistic cache update
export const useBookMarkMutation = (session, userId) => {
    const queryClient = useQueryClient();
    const mutation = useMutation({
        mutationFn: (data) => addBookmark(session?.access_token, data),

        onMutate: async(data) => {
            // Cancel in-flight queries
            queryClient.cancelQueries({ queryKey: ['journals'] });

            // Save previous state
            const previousData = queryClient.getQueriesData({ queryKey: ['journals'] });

            // Update cache optimistically across all journal queries
            queryClient.setQueriesData({ queryKey: ['journals'] }, (old) => 
                updateInfiniteJournalsCache(old, (journal) => {
                    if(journal.id !== data.journalId) return journal;
                    return {
                        ...journal,
                        has_bookmarked: !journal.has_bookmarked,
                        bookmark_count: [{count: newCount}]
                    };
                })
            );

            return {previousData};
        },

        onError: (err, data, context) => {
            // Rollback on error
            context?.previousData?.forEach(([key, value]) => {
                queryClient.setQueryData(key, value);
            });
        },

        onSettled: () => {
            // Final refresh
            queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['journals'] });
        }
    });
};
```

#### C. Stories Hooks (useStoryData.js)
```javascript
// Infinite pagination with timestamp-based cursor
export const useMyStories = (token) => {
    return useInfiniteQuery({
        queryKey: ['myStories'],
        queryFn: ({ pageParam }) => getMyStories(token, 5, pageParam),
        initialPageParam: undefined,
        getNextPageParam: (lastPage) => {
            if (lastPage.hasMore) {
                const lastStory = lastPage.data[lastPage.data.length - 1];
                return new Date(lastStory.updated_at).toISOString();  // ISO timestamp cursor
            }
            return undefined;
        },
        enabled: !!token,
        staleTime: 30000,
        refetchOnWindowFocus: false,
    });
};
```

#### D. Auth Context Query (Authcontext.jsx)
```javascript
// Session management
const {data: authData, isLoading: isAuthLoading} = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['authsession'],
    queryFn: async() => {
        const {data, error} = await supabase.auth.getSession();
        if(error) throw error;
        return data.session
    },
    staleTime: 1000 * 60 * 60,
    cacheTime: 1000 * 60 * 60,  // 1 hour cache
})

// User data with dependency
const {data: userData, isLoading} = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['userData', authData?.user?.id],
    queryFn: ({queryKey}) => getUserData(queryKey[1]),
    enabled: !!authData?.access_token,  // Depends on auth
    staleTime: 1000 * 60 * 60,
})
```

